doc.after: A map is a symbolic depiction highlighting relationships between elements of some space such as objects regions and themes  Many maps are static two dimensional geometrically accurate or approximately accurate representations of three dimensional space while others are dynamic or interactive even three dimensional Although most commonly used to depict geography maps may represent any space real or imagined without regard to context or scale e g brain mapping DNA mapping and extraterrestrial mapping
